
{"name":"Power Play","content":"<p>One of the highest authorities in the sector manages to turn everybody against you. How did they discredit you? And what’s their goal? You are their plaything; you may: buy their mercy with <strong>salary</strong> equal to your Tier +4 / face them (sacrifice all your <strong>reputation</strong and <strong>3 boons</strong>) / accept your judgement and be disbanded.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"thWDvNEhl7M3mC2d":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.WRuCjNaFeQAugpvY"}},"_id":"36o0ggbWhnUXu7Cy"}
{"name":"Nemesis","content":"<p>One of the most dangerous factions that you have opposed in the sector decides to crush you once and for all. You may: go to war against them / spend <strong>reputation</strong> or <strong>salary</strong> equal to their Tier +2 in order to have someone else deal with them.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"thWDvNEhl7M3mC2d":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.cxGl35wCdByk8N9x"}},"_id":"BJLd501vCFsJlrCN"}
{"name":"Cooperation","content":"<p>A +3 status faction asks you for a favor. You may: agree / lose <strong>rep</strong> equal to that faction’s Tier / lose <strong>1 status</strong> with them. If you have no +3 factions, no entanglement.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"thWDvNEhl7M3mC2d":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.xoz34R22ATadDztX"}},"_id":"Cy31qmwfzifm7DaZ"}
{"name":"Accusations","content":"<p>Someone influential persuades your master that your performance is less than adequate. You may: admit your failures (lose <strong>1 boon</strong> of your choice) / retort with accusations of your own (take <strong>suspicion</strong> equal to their Tier) / sacrifice all <strong>reputation</strong> and salary from the next operation in order to prove your virtue.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"thWDvNEhl7M3mC2d":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.nagSQyGbXzCv9bCw"}},"_id":"IJ5YyHTcpymRhkLQ"}
{"name":"Flipped","content":"<p>One of the PC’s rivals arranges for one of your contacts to no longer trust you.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"thWDvNEhl7M3mC2d":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.CXvqaOROYyqpWZpK"}},"_id":"NoLY64zJ3lEF5Xia"}
{"name":"Vengeance","content":"<p>An NPC (from a previous operation or from a PC’s past) is seeking to hurt or hinder you. Hire someone to deal with this, or do it personally.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"thWDvNEhl7M3mC2d":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.K1wg10vMiU0bOSsb"}},"_id":"dR9zBnrjy4AyA9Ru"}
{"name":"Unruly Cohort","content":"<p>One of your cohorts causes trouble due to their flaw(s). You may: publicly apologize (lose <strong>rep</strong equal to your Tier +1) / make an example of one of them / face reprisal from the wronged party.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"thWDvNEhl7M3mC2d":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.FZyfk6PnXl8pDltO"}}, "_id":"pEpm365I7XjEXeci"}
{"name":"Spreading Unrest","content":"<p>Rebellion and dissent are spreading across the sector, turning the populace against you. You may: ignore them (take <strong>suspicion</strong> equal to your Tier +1) / spend <strong>reputation</strong> equal to your Tier +1 to have the authority deal with them / personally take action against them.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"thWDvNEhl7M3mC2d":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.q0txK7pUnzstXrUy"}},"_id":"wVkkWR1jl10k7aeu"}
{"name":"Questioning","content":"<p>Your master interrogates one of your contacts in order to know more about your conduct. Who do they think knows more about you? Make a fortune roll to see if they reveal something about your <strong>corruptions (1-3: +2 suspicion; 4-5: +1 suspicion; 6: none)</strong> or buy their silence with <strong>salary</strong> equal to your Tier +2.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"thWDvNEhl7M3mC2d":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.XNuIDt1MjPKwISTW"}},"_id":"whBkmsxokUuJ4t9J"}
{"name":"Rivals","content":"<p>A neutral faction suddenly starts getting in your way whenever possible. You may: ignore them (lose <strong>rep or salary</strong> equal to their Tier) / face them (lose <strong>1 status</strong> with them).</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"thWDvNEhl7M3mC2d":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.K1wg10vMiU0bOSsb"}},"_id":"ADi9NxzmVOAueO2n"}


